1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.12eef45b-0e81-4dc5-aa85-f59d62d7ce6c.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.167c9171-d75e-4f2a-8efd-67d6dc2f6178.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Target. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.1f9d3426-c73a-4a7c-b52d-4b06b28566fb.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more
1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.21b9e661-5592-4252-a9cb-b78d05145d17.prompt=Username of the SA. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.2dac0f0a-7068-47bd-9efd-dcd2ad590c97.description=
This operation associate a target into the given TargetTier.
This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later.



Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.
coreVersion - [Optional] SA version. By default, it is the SA version being used.
admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment.
admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target.
admTargetTier - ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier.


Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
idAdmTargetTier - ADM Id of Application TargetTier.
admTargetTier - ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier.
server - Name of the SA managed server. It may have more than one server separated by ';'.


Responses\:
success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'
failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'
1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.35b5527f-4563-4096-8ff8-bdcf86868808.prompt=IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.45661f18-2a77-4317-8a29-8538aeba18ce.prompt=Name of the SA managed server. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.48a8573d-fdc0-4925-997d-e16f2d72951d.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.

This operation creates a new Target under given ADM Environment. 
This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later.



Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.
coreVersion - [Optional] SA version. By default, it is the SA version being used.
admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment.
admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target.


Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
idAdmTarget - ADM Id of Application Target.
admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target.
idAdmEnvironment - ADM Id of Application Environment.
admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment.


Responses\:
success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'
failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'

1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.b05ca4c3-45b3-43c4-9ad4-10c845b28a92.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.c05f9c15-4d1e-4a61-a909-4b6837dd5029.description=
This operation adds/removes a SA managed server (given in the input parameter 'server') to/from the ADM TargetTier.
This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later.



Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.
coreVersion - [Optional] SA version. By default, it is the SA version being used.
admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment.
admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target.
admTargetTier - ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier.
server - Name of the SA managed server.
actionType - [Optional] Add or Remove. It can be one of [add, remove]. By default it is 'add'


Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
idAdmTargetTier - ADM Id of Application TargetTier.
admTargetTier - ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier.
server - Name of the SA managed server. It may have more than one server separated by ';'.


Responses\:
success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'
failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'
1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.c5f63ad6-bedf-4fde-ab45-cdc21f9a64d9.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.c95469db-bba1-4a92-855a-fadaf497e6d3.prompt=Password of SA user. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.cbe9daac-260e-4a07-a79f-1297319f16ee.prompt=Password of SA user. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.d7f8b588-7baf-4f05-aca2-95c280a4fbcf.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Target. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.db927ed4-eeeb-4ec9-8fcd-e2e46b205cd6.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. 1809b9d6-ace1-4497-b5b2-9c1f4ed57a6a.description=
Create a target in Server Automation's Application Deployment Manager(ADM). The purpose of a target is to define the set of machines to which an application will be deployed.


Inputs\:
coreHost - the host running ADM that you want to connect to
coreUsername - user name to use when connecting to ADM
corePassword - the password to use when connecting to ADM 
admEnvironment - name of ADM Application Environment.
admTarget - name of ADM Application Target.
appTierServerMapping -  "\#" separated list of comma "," separated server values of application tier and each mapping separated by a "^" . 
For ex\:Tier1\#server1,server2,server3^tier2\#server4,server5,server6 -> where server1,server2 maps to Tier1 and server4,server5 maps to Tier2

Responses\:
   success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0
   failure - otherwise
